question:
Analyze the following code snippet. Identify the potential issue and explain how the multiple catch clauses handle different exception scenarios. Provide a corrected version if necessary.

```java
try {
    int[] numbers = new int[5];
    numbers[10] = 30 / 0;
} catch (Exception e) {
    System.out.println("A general exception occurred");
} catch (ArithmeticException e) {
    System.out.println("Cannot divide by zero");
} catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
    System.out.println("Array index is out of bounds");
}
```
